    scienceNotes: "CJC-1295 DAC (modified GHRH 1-29 + Drug Affinity Complex, MW ~3647 Da) was developed by ConjuChem Biotechnologies. Teichman et al. Phase 2 trial (J Clin Endocrinol Metab 2006, DOI: 10.1210/jc.2005-2664, N=56 healthy adults): single SC dose increased mean GH 2-10x for 6+ days, IGF-1 1.5-3x for 9-11 days. DAC forms thioether bond with albumin Cys34, confirmed by SEC-HPLC (>90% conjugation within 15 min). Four AA substitutions confer DPP-IV resistance. Functional t1/2 ~6-8 days via albumin binding (albumin t1/2 ~19 days). No significant glucose/insulin changes or receptor desensitization observed. AEs: injection site reactions, flushing, headache.",
